column5: We had a blast tonight fishing for less than 2 hours off a dock.  We managed 10 fish (nothing big but lots of fun)  2.4 pounds was the largest. Crazy double header smallie bullhead all interupted by a phone call in the middle of it.  Too funny. Lots of fun and I will do it again soon. 2.4 pounder  Strange double header  Last cast of the night   I also fished the same area this aft from my boat and lost a big fish but still managed 5 smallies and a bunch of perch. nice little fat fish
Good to see you're hammering away at some bass.

I have heard of nighttime largies but not smallies, guess I need to get out more LOL.   Thanks for the report and pictures! I bet you would not believe me but I caught a catfish at night on a bass popper, literally when it hit the water...  MTBF
Geez, if this is in Barrie gimme a ring before you head out
Great job Cudz Got to love the night time bite for Smallies Thanks for sharing Leechman
Gotta love the night bite! Up here the bugs get too wild this time of year to really enjoy that kind of dock action after dark though...
Looks like a good time bud! Nice job!
